               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>A sample of Sāñcīpat, Agar wood bark prepared to be used as writing support. This practice is common in Assam. Most folios are blank, except for <locus facs="10">one</locus> which contains a few lines in Śāradā script.</p>
<p>A <locus facs="2">note</locus> in Palmyr Cordier's hand describes the process by which the folios are prepared, translated into French from an <ref target="https://archive.org/details/journalofasiatic6318asia/page/107/mode/1up">1894 article</ref> in the Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal by E. A. Gait.</p></summary>
                  
